Vertical columns: column 1 covered by 7 and 1, column 2 by 5, column 3 by none. So vertical column 3 isn't covered. Therefore, incomplete. Therefore, three squares are necessary. The hitting set of size three works. Therefore, the minimal number of guesses required is three. But wait, the problem says "Find at least one square that is covered by the rectangle". So the strategy is to guess the three squares in the hitting set. If the rectangle is found in one of those guesses, then we have covered it.
